      "is_accepted": false,
      "score": 0,
      "last_activity_date": 1762748428,
      "creation_date": 1762748428,
      "answer_id": 79815188,
      "question_id": 79814934,
      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>In this case, skip the assert because, as you correctly stated, the assert will never fail because the wait will timeout first. I would say that it's a good practice to assert when you need to validate but as you've seen, in this case a literal <code>Assert</code> isn't needed.</p>\n"
